{
  "text": "Hemiplegia is a common residual deficit in stroke survivors. The hemiplegic shoulders exhibited significantly more sonographic abnormalities than the unaffected shoulders and the control shoulders, which is in agreement with the findings of previous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . These results show that hemiplegia caused significant shoulder soft tissue damage in the recruited stroke survivors, with a mean of approximately three sonographic abnormalities per hemiplegic shoulder, which was not observed in the ageand sex-matched controls.",
  "correct_citation": {
